race.comment: NICOFFHOME (3) is going much better than form suggests. Only a few lengths away last time and looks very well placed here at the extra ground. Will take running down. VINEUX (4) is coming off a big maiden win last time over 2600m at Cranbourne. Tricky gate but doubt this is much tougher and now found form can go on with it. PARABELLUM (8) is going better than it looks, getting back and running on late. Well weighted with the claim and should be tough to hold out over the extra ground now. HOLLY'S STAR (1) gave too big a start last time. Will fins this much easier and form is better than it looks. Can do better over the longer journey this time.
